    "Id": "192075",
    "ThreadId": "56317",
    "Html": "<p>Your DataGrid column, let's assume it's a DataGridTextColumn, should have a Binding property set to {Binding Path=DisplayValue}. Then, you don't need to specify any template.</p>\r\n<p>If you are using a DataGridTemplateColumn, then in your template, your TextBlock will have Text=&quot;{Binding Path=DisplayValue}&quot;.</p>\r\n<p>There should be no need to use index in any of the bindings since that should be taken care of when each row is generated.</p>\r\n<p>Ben</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2009-05-19T13:36:14.397-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
